    "These challenges are well-documented in the literature, see e.g., (Finley et al., 2019; Liu et al., 1994).",
    "In particular, two main computational bottlenecks arise: (i) the high dimensionality of the latent field w, and (ii) the repeated inversion of dense n × n covariance matrices needed to evaluate the full conditional distributions.",
    "To address the computational bottleneck caused by the repeated inversion of the n × n covariance matrix, we propose applying the Vecchia approximation to the latent spatial process w.",
    "The Vecchia approximation is based on rewriting the joint density of the latent vector w as a product of conditional densities:",
    "where v(i) = {1,."
